# Agentic AI Infrastructure Management System

An intelligent agent that autonomously plans, provisions, and manages AWS infrastructure with specialized focus on Kubernetes cluster deployment and application lifecycle management.

## üöÄ Overview

This system operates as an intelligent infrastructure companion that:
- Analyzes application requirements from Git repositories
- Plans optimal AWS infrastructure using Well-Architected Framework principles
- Generates Infrastructure as Code (Terraform/CDK)
- Provisions and manages Kubernetes clusters
- Deploys applications with proper monitoring and security
- Continuously optimizes performance and costs

## üîß Core Capabilities

### Infrastructure Planning & Architecture
- ‚úÖ AWS Well-Architected Framework compliance
- ‚úÖ High availability multi-AZ deployments
- ‚úÖ EKS cluster management with security configurations
- ‚úÖ VPC design with proper network segmentation

### LangGraph Integration
- ‚úÖ Topology visualization and planning workflows
- ‚úÖ Decision-making process modeling
- ‚úÖ Impact analysis for infrastructure changes
- ‚úÖ Automated compliance checking

### Security & IAM Management
- ‚úÖ Root credential usage only for initial setup
- ‚úÖ Role-based access control with least-privilege
- ‚úÖ Automated security scanning and compliance
- ‚úÖ Secrets management integration

### Application Deployment Intelligence
- ‚úÖ Git repository analysis and dependency mapping
- ‚úÖ Infrastructure requirements assessment
- ‚úÖ Deployment strategy planning (blue/green, canary, rolling)
- ‚úÖ Auto-scaling and resource optimization

